
quattor-sw-util: a collection of Perl utilities for generating Pan templates
describing the RPM packages to be managed by Quattor.

Author: 
	Charles A. Loomis, Jr. -> comps2pan, html2pan, html2updates and rpmcheck
	Marco Emilio Poleggi <Marco.Poleggi@cern.ch> -> rpmq2pan_pkg

###############################################################################
comps2pan:
	transform a comps.xml file (used to describe package groups for RedHat-like
	systems) into a set of PAN templates suitable for use with quattor.

html2pan:
	generate valid repository PAN templates from an rpm repository which 
	already exists in an HTTP server.

html2updates:
	similar to html2pan, but create a list of "updates".

rpmcheck:
	check that the rpm list in a generated LLD file is complete.

rpmq2pan_pkg:
	generate Pan software package templates from the local RPM database 
	contents.

